sbpro-card
    .card-header Combining Border Utilities
    .card-body
        h6.small.text-muted.fw-500 Basic Combinations:
        .border.border-lg.rounded.mb-4
            .p-4.border-bottom
                .row.gx-4
                    .col-6
                        .bg-light.border-start.border-lg.rounded.border-primary.p-3.mb-3 Combine border position, radius, color, and thickness utilities!
                        .bg-light.border-top.border-lg.rounded.border-warning.p-3 Combine border position, radius, color, and thickness utilities!
                    .col-6
                        .bg-light.border-end.border-lg.rounded.border-secondary.p-3.mb-3 Combine border position, radius, color, and thickness utilities!
                        .bg-light.border-bottom.border-lg.rounded.border-danger.p-3 Combine border position, radius, color, and thickness utilities!

            .bg-light.p-4.small
                | By combining utility classes, you can avoid creating your own custom components, saving time and decresing CSS bloat throughout your project!
                
        h6.small.text-muted.fw-500 Modified Cards:
        .border.border-lg.rounded.mb-4
            .p-4.border-bottom
                .row.gx-4
                    .col-6
                        sbpro-card([classes]='["sb-border-left-lg", "border-primary"]')
                            .card-body
                                | This is a custom card with a thick, colored border.
                        sbpro-card([classes]='["sb-border-top-lg", "border-warning"]')
                            .card-body
                                | This is a custom card with a thick, colored border.
                    .col-6
                        sbpro-card([classes]='["sb-border-right-lg", "border-secondary"]')
                            .card-body
                                | This is a custom card with a thick, colored border.
                        sbpro-card([classes]='["sb-border-bottom-lg", "border-danger"]')
                            .card-body
                                | This is a custom card with a thick, colored border.

            .bg-light.p-4.small
                | Use utility classes to modify the style of components on the fly! You don't need to use the default border utility classes if the component already has a border by default.
            
        h6.small.text-muted.fw-500 Modified Alerts:
        .border.border-lg.rounded
            .p-4.border-bottom
                sbpro-alert([icon]='true', [classes]='["alert-primary", "sb-border-left-lg"]', heading='Primary Icon Alert')
                    .alert-icon-aside
                        fa-icon([icon]='["far", "bell"]')
                    | This alert has a thick left border!
                
                sbpro-alert([icon]='true', [classes]='["alert-secondary", "sb-border-top-lg", "mb-0"]', heading='Primary Icon Alert')
                    .alert-icon-aside
                        fa-icon([icon]='["far", "bell"]')
                    | This alert has a thick left border!

            .bg-light.p-4.small
                | Any element that already has a border defined by default doesn't need to use the Bootstrap border utilities!
